IS  - 0340-6717 (Linking)
VI  - 104
IP  - 1
DP  - 1999 Jan
TI  - P57 (KIP2) polymorphisms and breast cancer risk.
PG  - 83-8
AB  - A previous report in this journal has suggested that germline deletions in the 
      proline-alanine-rich (PAPA-repeat) region of P57 (KIP2) are associated with 
      increased risk of a variety of cancers, including breast cancer. We have analyzed 
      the association of P57 PAPA-repeat deletion polymorphisms and breast cancer risk 
      as part of a population-based case-control study of breast cancer. We have not 
      observed an association between the presence of one or two copies of deletion 
      polymorphisms in P57 and breast cancer risk (adjusted odds ratio: 1.1, 95% 
      confidence interval: 0.6-2.0). Further investigation is necessary to determine 
      the functional significance of P57 deletion polymorphisms and their potential 
      relationship with disease.
