TI  - Beyond fibrocystic disease. The evolving concept of pre-malignant breast disease.
PG  - 173-8
AB  - There is a broad spectrum of benign and pre-malignant breast disease that may be 
      diagnosed on biopsy. Some of these conditions place affected women at 
      significantly increased risk for breast cancer, particularly the atypical 
      hyperplasias. All health care workers should be aware of recent developments in 
      this important aspect of breast disease. The classification, criteria for 
      diagnosis, associated risks for cancer development and various controversies 
      related to these benign and borderline breast diseases are discussed.
