TI  - [Generic screening for breast cancer].
PG  - 369-71
AB  - Following the cloning of BRCA1 and BRCA2 it has been suggested that genetic 
      screening may be of benefit for women at high familial risk. To be able to assess 
      whether this is the case more research is needed on the penetrance of the 
      different mutations, their prevalence in the population, the biological and 
      environmental factors affecting the development of cancer in mutation carriers 
      and the natural history of genetically determined breast cancer. Furthermore, 
      studies on the efficacy of preventive measures, on counselling and on 
      psychological effects of testing are also needed.
