TI  - [BRCA1 and BRCA2: mutations and other genetic changes--practical relevance].
PG  - 373-9
AB  - Genetic predisposition is responsible for 5-10% of all breast cancer. Within the 
      past 10 years the major susceptibility genes for breast cancer, BRCA1 and BRCA2, 
      have been identified. Both genes are considered to be tumor-suppressor genes, but 
      their function is poorly understood. Current genetic testing for mutated BRCA1 
      and BRCA2 is the basis for estimating disease risk for women with a strong family 
      history of breast cancer and will provide important information on the prevention 
      and treatment of familial breast cancer.
