DP  - 1999 Jun
TI  - Breast cancer stage cost analysis in a managed care population. Based on a 
      presentation by Kenneth L. McDonough, MD, MS.
PG  - S377-82
AB  - A sample managed care plan provides the framework for examining data on breast 
      cancer, employing a naturalistic setting as opposed to the randomized control 
      trial model. Breast cancer costs are analyzed by disease stage, which is broken 
      down further by treatment phase. This approach compares the costs of those with 
      treated disease to a control group, essentially performing a case mix adjustment 
      for comorbidities. Such an approach encompasses the claims database 
      characteristics, defines the breast cancer stages and treatment phases, and 
      describes the criteria used for the control group, as well as the methodology 
      utilized in the case mix adjustment.
