VI  - 27
IP  - 7-8
DP  - 1999 Jul-Aug
TI  - [Genetic predisposition to breast cancer: a review in April 1998].
PG  - 517-20
AB  - The recent identification of the BRCA1 and BRCA2 genes allows to understand in an 
      increasing number of cases the origin of a breast/ovarian cancer family history 
      and thereby to propose genetic testing to at risk women. However to know to be 
      carrier of a predisposing germline mutation is at the present to deal with the 
      difficult choice of different supportive cares: close follow up or prophylactic 
      surgery. Numerous studies still have to be done to determine the better 
      management of women at risk. The other challenges are the understanding of the 
      origin of each breast or ovarian cancer case; to identify the factors which 
      modify the tumor risks in predisposed women; and finally to win the social 
      acceptance of genetic testing avoiding any discrimination.
