DP  - 1999 Jan
TI  - Retention of polysomy at 9p23-24 during karyotypic evolution in human breast 
      cancer cell line COLO 824.
PG  - 87-93
AB  - Somatic genetic alterations of 9p have been seen in a wide range of human 
      cancers, including breast cancer. Loss of heterozygosity analysis of primary 
      breast cancer tumors has revealed a high frequency of deletion of DNA from 
      9p21-22 encompassing the MTSI (P16/CDKN2A) gene. We report the approximately 
      tenfold increase in copy number of DNA from 9p23-24, which is far distal to 
      P16/CDKN2A in female breast cancer cell line COLO 824, as revealed by 
      fluorescence in situ hybridization, comparative genomic hybridization, and 
      microsatellite analysis. Amplification of DNA has been reported previously to 
      encompass multiple sites of the genome of the breast cancer cell, but increase in 
      DNA copy number has not been seen in distal 9p.
