DP  - 1999 Jun 1
TI  - Identification of a novel gene, DAM1, amplified at chromosome 1p13.3-21 region in 
      human breast cancer cell lines.
PG  - 219-26
AB  - Screening for differentially expressed genes in cancer cell lines by the RNA 
      differential display (DD) technique identified a novel mRNA that encodes a 26-kDa 
      protein and is up-regulated in MCF-7 and BT-20 breast cancer cells. The predicted 
      amino acid sequence showed 38% homology to Caenorhabditis elegans T12A2.7 
      protein, indicating that this is a possible human homologue for C. elegans 
      T12A2.7 protein. The mRNA, designated DAM1 (DNA amplified in mammary carcinoma), 
      was mapped at the 1p13.3-21 region, which is frequently altered in human breast 
      cancer. By Southern blot analysis, we confirmed that the up-regulation of this 
      novel gene is associated with gene amplification in MCF-7 (10-fold) and BT-20 
      (5-fold) cells. Our findings suggest that the DAM1 gene is a novel gene 
      up-regulated by amplification in human breast cancer cell lines.
