TI  - Genetic analysis of BRCA1 function in a defined tumor cell line.
PG  - 1093-9
AB  - Retrovirally expressed, wild-type BRCA1 decreased the gamma radiation (IR) 
      sensitivity and increased the efficiency of double-strand DNA break repair (DSBR) 
      of the BRCA1-/- human breast cancer line, HCC1937. It also reduced its 
      susceptibility to DSB generation by IR. By contrast, multiple, clinically 
      validated, missense mutant BRCA1 products were nonfunctional in these assays. 
      These data constitute the basis for a BRCA1 functional assay and suggest that 
      efficient repair of double-strand DNA breaks is linked to BRCA1 tumor suppression 
      function.
