TI  - Induction of AP-1 activity by perillyl alcohol in breast cancer cells.
PG  - 1957-61
AB  - Monoterpenes display chemopreventive and therapeutic activity in rat mammary 
      tumor models. Monoterpenes can also inhibit cell growth and induce apoptosis of 
      cultured cells. In this study, the monoterpene perillyl alcohol (POH) was found 
      to induce transient expression of the c-jun and c-fos genes transcriptionally. 
      POH also transiently induced phosphorylation of c-Jun protein. These events were 
      associated with transcriptional activation of an AP-1-dependent reporter gene. 
      These results suggest that POH might affect c-Jun activity via the Jun N-terminal 
      kinase/stress-activated protein kinase pathway and modulate expression of AP-1 
      target genes.
