DP  - 1999 Jun
TI  - The Prophylactic Mastectomy Dilemma: A Support Group for Women at High Genetic 
      Risk for Breast Cancer.
PG  - 163-73
LID - 10.1023/A:1022834706495 [doi]
AB  - The goal of this pilot study was to test the usefulness of a six session 
      psychoeducational support group for women at high genetic risk for breast cancer 
      who were considering prophylactic mastectomy. The themes of the group sessions 
      included overestimation of and anxiety about risk; desire for "hard data"; the 
      emotional impact of watching a mother die of breast cancer; concerns about spouse 
      reactions; self- and body image; the decision-making process; and confusion over 
      whom to trust in decision making. Both the participants and the multidisciplinary 
      leaders concluded that as a supplement to individual counseling, a support group 
      is a beneficial and cost-effective treatment modality. Recommendations for the 
      optimal format for such a group are described.
