TI  - Evaluating GA733-2 mRNA as a marker for the detection of micrometastatic breast 
      cancer in peripheral blood and bone marrow.
PG  - 2-6
AB  - The GA733-2 gene encodes the epithelial glycoprotein 40, a homophilic cell-cell 
      adhesion molecule, which is expressed on the surface of epithelial cells and 
      associated with a variety of carcinomas, e.g. breast, colorectal and lung 
      carcinomas. To test if it could serve as a tumor marker, we have analysed the 
      expression of GA733-2 in bone marrow (BM) and peripheral blood (PB) from healthy 
      donors, and of patients with haematological malignancies or breast cancer using 
      reverse transcriptase-polymerase chain reaction (RT-PCR). The GA733-2 nested PCR 
      was positive in 100% (8/8) of BM and 40% (16/40) of PB from healthy donors, in 
      100% (33/33) of BM from patients with breast cancer who had no evidence of 
      distant metastases and also in BM and PB from patients with haematological 
      malignancies. GA733-2 mRNA is not specific as a marker for the detection of 
      breast cancer cells in BM and PB.
